   <article class="post-298 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-migration" id="post-298">
    <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/26/preparing-for-the-move/">
     <div class="date-tab">
      <span class="month">
       May
      </span>
      <span class="day">
       26
      </span>
     </div>
     <!-- .date-tab -->
    </a>
    <h1>
     <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/26/preparing-for-the-move/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Preparing for the Move">
      Preparing for the Move
     </a>
    </h1>
    <div class="post-inner">
     <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/26/preparing-for-the-move/">
     </a>
     <p>
      <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/files/2015/05/Box-on-Wheels75518110-small.jpg">
       <img alt="" class="alignright size-full wp-image-302" height="181" src="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/files/2015/05/Box-on-Wheels75518110-small.jpg" title="Cardboard Box With Standard Signs And Wheels Isolated On White" width="288"/>
      </a>
      At 5:00 PM Central Standard Time on Thursday, May 28, the content – including images, forms and files – of all sites in blogs.rice.edu will be frozen in read-only mode in preparation for the migration May 29-31.  During the migration, your entire site will be zipped up, moved to its new home, and unpacked for you, retaining the same domain name and links you currently use.
     </p>
     <p>
      Yes! Your readers can still view all your content during the migration.  For additional details on the migration, see  our “
      <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/18/may-28-migration-what-to-expect/" title="May 28 Migration – What to Expect">
       What to Expect
      </a>
      ” post.
     </p>
     <p>
     </p>
     <div addthis:title="Preparing for the Move " addthis:url="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/26/preparing-for-the-move/" class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style addthis_32x32_style">
      <a class="addthis_button_preferred_1">
      </a>
