   <article class="post-282 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-update" id="post-282">
    <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/18/may-28-migration-what-to-expect/">
     <div class="date-tab">
      <span class="month">
       May
      </span>
      <span class="day">
       18
      </span>
     </div>
     <!-- .date-tab -->
    </a>
    <h1>
     <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/18/may-28-migration-what-to-expect/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to May 28 Migration – What to Expect">
      May 28 Migration – What to Expect
     </a>
    </h1>
    <div class="post-inner">
     <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/18/may-28-migration-what-to-expect/">
     </a>
     <p>
      <strong>
       <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/files/2015/05/Migration-bigstock-Good-Duck-Service-81654131.jpg">
        <img alt="" class="alignright size-full wp-image-288" height="279" src="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/files/2015/05/Migration-bigstock-Good-Duck-Service-81654131.jpg" title="Good Duck Service" width="288"/>
       </a>
       EduBlogs Migration May 28-31
      </strong>
     </p>
     <p>
      The university’s general purpose blogging and content management system, blogs.rice.edu, is moving to a more robust WordPress platform with many popular themes, plug-ins, widgets and other features.  Rice University has contracted with CampusPress by EduBlogs to provide the new cloud-hosted environment.  Details on the new features can be found in
      <a href="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/">
       http://about.blogs.rice.edu
      </a>
      .
     </p>
     <p>
      Over the weekend of May 28-31, the full contents of blogs.rice.edu will be moved into the new CampusPress environment.
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       The new platform will retain the previous domain names at blogs.rice.edu.
      </li>
      <li>
       The old Rice blogs platform will be renamed oldblogs.rice.edu and content archived “as is.”
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p>
      What you can expect during the migration:
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       Content is still visible to your readers
      </li>
      <li>
       Content is frozen in read-only mode (can’t be edited during migration)
      </li>
      <li>
       For emergence content updates, contact the Help Desk:
       <a href="mailto:helpdesk@rice.edu">
        helpdesk@rice.edu
       </a>
       or 713.348.4357.
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p>
      <strong>
       In preparation for the migration, OIT is performing a test on Tuesday, May 19 between 5:00 and 5:30 PM.
      </strong>
      <br/>
      What you can expect during the test:
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       Content is still visible to your readers
      </li>
      <li>
       Content is frozen in read-only mode (can’t be edited during migration)
      </li>
      <li>
       For emergence content updates, contact the Help Desk:
       <a href="mailto:helpdesk@rice.edu">
        helpdesk@rice.edu
       </a>
       or 713.348.4357.
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p>
      Thank you for your patience as we prepare your content for its new home.
     </p>
     <div addthis:title="May 28 Migration – What to Expect " addthis:url="http://about.blogs.rice.edu/2015/05/18/may-28-migration-what-to-expect/" class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style addthis_32x32_style">
      <a class="addthis_button_preferred_1">
